<div class='brown_comment'>
<span class="loadingLinkSpan"><a class="loadingLink" data-remote="true" href="/review/1137689694/comments?reverse=true">View all 58 comments</a><span class="loadingAnimation"></span><span class="loadingError"></span></span>
</div>
<div id="comment_234792506" class="brown_comment">
  <div class="xhr_comment_photo">
    	<a alt="Steven" href="/user/show/49481692-steven"><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1529144209p1/49481692.jpg" alt="49481692" /></a>
  </div>
  <div class="xhr_comment_body">
    <a style="font-weight:bold" href="/user/show/49481692-steven">Steven</a>

      
<span id="freeTextContainer6355130404164387541">Im still thinking about this at times. Don&apos;t you think it is possible that there was no authorial intent in some of Wyndham&apos;s decisions but that he si</span>
  <span id="freeText6355130404164387541" style="display:none">Im still thinking about this at times. Don't you think it is possible that there was no authorial intent in some of Wyndham's decisions but that he simply let the story unfold in a way that would lead to the most exciting conflicts?</span>
  <a data-text-id="6355130404164387541" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

    <br/>

